## 3. AUTK-MAP: 3D/2D RENDERING

### Installation & Setup
```typescript
import { AutkMap, LayerType } from 'autk-map';

const canvas = document.querySelector('canvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
const map = new AutkMap(canvas, autoResize = true);
await map.init();
map.draw(); // Start 60fps render loop
```

### Layer Types

| LayerType | Geometry | Purpose |
|-----------|----------|---------|
| `AUTK_OSM_SURFACE` | Polygon | Ground/land cover |
| `AUTK_OSM_PARKS` | Polygon | Parks/green areas |
| `AUTK_OSM_WATER` | Polygon | Water bodies |
| `AUTK_OSM_ROADS` | Polyline | Road network |
| `AUTK_OSM_BUILDINGS` | Polygon | 3D buildings (height from OSM tags) |
| `AUTK_GEO_POINTS` | Point/MultiPoint | Custom points |
| `AUTK_GEO_POLYLINES` | LineString/MultiLineString | Custom lines |
| `AUTK_GEO_POLYGONS` | Polygon/MultiPolygon | Custom polygons |
| `AUTK_RASTER` | Grid-based | Heatmaps, GeoTIFF |

### Loading Layers

```typescript
// Auto-detect geometry type
map.loadGeoJsonLayer('neighborhoods', geojson);

// Explicit type
map.loadGeoJsonLayer('buildings', geojson, LayerType.AUTK_OSM_BUILDINGS);

// From autk-db
for (const layer of db.getLayerTables()) {
  const geojson = await db.getLayer(layer.name);
  map.loadGeoJsonLayer(layer.name, geojson, layer.type as LayerType);
}

// Raster/heatmap
map.loadGeoTiffLayer('elevation', geotiffFeatureCollection, LayerType.AUTK_RASTER);
```

### Bounding Box
```typescript
// Auto-set from first layer's bbox property
// Or manually set before loading layers:
map.boundingBox = [minLon, minLat, maxLon, maxLat];

// Get current bbox
const bbox = map.boundingBox;
```

### Styling

```typescript
// Opacity (0.0 transparent, 1.0 opaque)
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'opacity', 0.7);

// Color map interpolator
import { ColorMapInterpolator } from 'autk-map';
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'colorMapInterpolator', ColorMapInterpolator.SEQUENTIAL_REDS);

// Available interpolators:
// - SEQUENTIAL_REDS (light to dark red, default)
// - SEQUENTIAL_BLUES (light to dark blue)
// - DIVERGING_RED_BLUE (red-blue for positive/negative)
// - OBSERVABLE10 (10-color categorical)

// Color map labels (legend)
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'colorMapLabels', ['0 m', '50 m']);

// Enable/disable thematic coloring
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'isColorMap', true);
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'isColorMap', false);
```

### Thematic Mapping

```typescript
const geojson = await db.getLayer('buildings');

// By numeric attribute
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'colorMapInterpolator', ColorMapInterpolator.SEQUENTIAL_REDS);
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'isColorMap', true);

map.updateGeoJsonLayerThematic(
  'buildings',
  geojson,
  (feature) => feature.properties?.height ?? 0
);

// By categorical attribute
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('roads', 'colorMapInterpolator', ColorMapInterpolator.OBSERVABLE10);

map.updateGeoJsonLayerThematic(
  'roads',
  geojson,
  (feature) => {
    const hw = feature.properties?.highway;
    return ['primary', 'secondary'].includes(hw) ? hw : 'other';
  }
);

// Buildings with groupById (color entire building by one value)
map.updateGeoJsonLayerThematic(
  'buildings',
  geojson,
  (feature) => feature.properties?.floor_count ?? 0,
  true // groupById
);
```

### Interactions

#### Picking (Click to Select)
```typescript
import { MapEvent } from 'autk-map';

// Enable picking
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'isPick', true);

// Listen for picks
map.mapEvents.on(MapEvent.PICK, (selectedIds, layerId) => {
  console.log(`Selected IDs on layer "${layerId}":`, selectedIds);
  // selectedIds: array of internal component IDs
  // empty array = clicked empty space (deselected)
});
```

#### Show/Hide Layer
```typescript
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('parks', 'isSkip', true); // hide
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('parks', 'isSkip', false); // show
```

#### Update Geometry
```typescript
map.updateLayerGeometry('buildings', newGeometryData);
// Low-level API - usually better to reload with loadGeoJsonLayer
```

### Camera & Mouse Events
```typescript
// Access camera
const camera = map.camera;

// Mouse events (pan, zoom, rotate) are handled internally
// Keyboard events available via KeyEvents class
// Mouse events via MouseEvents class
```

